{"step_by_step_thinking": "Alpha-fetoprotein (AFP) is a protein produced by the liver and yolk sac of a developing baby during pregnancy. Omphalocele and gastroschisis are birth defects of the abdominal wall, but they are not specifically associated with high levels of AFP.
